# WHAT IT IS
#   `dicom-dump` is the Rust ecosystem's reference DICOM file
#   inspector — the equivalent of OFFIS dcmtk's `dcmdump` (the
#   canonical C++ DICOM dumper in continuous use across every
#   PACS shop since the 1990s).  Reads one or more `.dcm` files
#   and prints every Data Element with:
#
#     • The DICOM Tag `(0008,0018)` style (group + element
#       hex pair, plus the standard-dictionary name like
#       `SOPInstanceUID` resolved via dicom-dictionary-std)
#
#     • The Value Representation (VR) — one of the 27 typed VR
#       enums (`AE` Application Entity, `AS` Age String, `AT`
#       Attribute Tag, `CS` Code String, `DA` Date, `DS`
#       Decimal String, `DT` Date Time, `FL` Float, `FD`
#       Double, `IS` Integer String, `LO` Long String, `LT`
#       Long Text, `OB` Other Byte, `OD` Other Double, `OF`
#       Other Float, `OL` Other Long, `OV` Other Very-long,
#       `OW` Other Word, `PN` Person Name, `SH` Short String,
#       `SL` Signed Long, `SQ` Sequence of Items, `SS` Signed
#       Short, `ST` Short Text, `SV` Signed Very-long, `TM`
#       Time, `UC` Unlimited Characters, `UI` Unique Identifier,
#       `UL` Unsigned Long, `UN` Unknown, `UR` URI/URL, `US`
#       Unsigned Short, `UT` Unlimited Text, `UV` Unsigned
#       Very-long)
#
#     • The Value Length (VL — encoded length of the element's
#       value field, including handling for the special
#       0xFFFFFFFF "undefined length" sentinel used in
#       sequences + pixel-data fragments)
#
#     • The decoded value (with smart truncation for long text
#       blobs / pixel-data arrays / private-tag opaque blobs;
#       Sequence-of-Items VR (`SQ`) is recursively expanded with
#       indented nested-item printing)
#
#   Output formats:
#     • Human-readable colorized text (default) — owo-colors-
#       driven palette, ANSI escapes wrapped to terminal width
#       (auto-detected via terminal_size)
#     • DICOM-JSON (`--format json`) — the standard DICOM
#       JSON encoding from PS3.18 Annex F (each Tag becomes a
#       JSON object with `vr` + `Value` keys, sequences are
#       recursively encoded as arrays of nested objects, BulkData
#       URIs are emitted for OB/OW/OD/OF/UN fragments)
#
# CLI ARGUMENT GRAMMAR  (verbatim from dump/src/main.rs
#                       clap-derive `App` struct; extracted via
#                       raw.githubusercontent.com fetch of
#                       dump/src/main.rs)
#
#   dicom-dump [OPTIONS] <FILE>...
#
#   Arguments:
#     <FILE>...                      DICOM file(s) to read (one
#                                    or more `.dcm` files)
#
#   Options:
#     -h, --help                     Show help
#     -V, --version                  Print version
#     --until <TAG>                  Read the file only up to
#                                    this DICOM Tag (e.g.
#                                    `(7FE0,0010)` or
#                                    `PixelData`)
#     -o, --odd-length-strategy <STRATEGY>
#                                    Strategy for handling odd-
#                                    length text values
#                                    [default: accept]
#                                    [values: accept, next_even,
#                                             fail]
#         accept                     Accept elements with an odd
#                                    length as-is, continuing
#                                    data-set reading normally
#         next_even                  Assume the real length is
#                                    `length + 1` (next even
#                                    number)
#         fail                       Raise an error instead
#     --no-text-limit                Print text values to the
#                                    end (limited to `width` by
#                                    default; does not apply if
#                                    output is not a tty or
#                                    output is JSON)
#     --no-limit                     Print all values to the
#                                    end (implies
#                                    `--no-text-limit`,
#                                    limited to `width` by
#                                    default)
#     -w, --width <N>                Display width
#                                    (default: auto-detected
#                                    via terminal_size, or 120
#                                    if non-tty;  does not apply
#                                    if output is JSON)
#     --color <MODE>                 Color mode
#                                    [default: auto]
#                                    [values: auto, always,
#                                             never]
#     --fail-first                   Fail if any errors are
#                                    encountered (default
#                                    behavior is to keep going
#                                    when multiple files are
#                                    given)
#     -f, --format <FORMAT>          Output format
#                                    [default: text]
#                                    [values: text, json]
#
# AXIS / CORPUS POSITION
#   `Enet4/dicom-rs/dump` declares **direct** dependencies on
#   `dicom-core`, `dicom-encoding`, `dicom-json`, `dicom-object`,
#   `dicom-transfer-syntax-registry`, `dicom-dictionary-std`
#   (all members of the Enet4/dicom-rs workspace) in its
#   `Cargo.toml` (verified via `gh api repos/Enet4/dicom-rs/
#   contents/dump/Cargo.toml`).
#
#   `Enet4/dicom-rs` is **THE canonical Rust DICOM library** —
#   Eduardo Pinho's reference pure-Rust implementation of the
#   NEMA PS3 DICOM standard, in continuous active development
#   since 2017 with 543+ ★ on GitHub.  It ships as a multi-
#   crate workspace covering every layer of the DICOM stack:
#
#     • `dicom-core`                 the typed `DataElement`
#                                    primitives,
#                                    `Tag(group, element)`,
#                                    `VR::*` enum, `Value::*`
#                                    discriminated union,
#                                    `PrimitiveValue::*`
#                                    typed value-encoding
#                                    enum
#     • `dicom-encoding`             the typed wire-format
#                                    encoders + decoders for
#                                    every DICOM Transfer
#                                    Syntax (Implicit VR Little
#                                    Endian, Explicit VR Little
#                                    Endian, Explicit VR Big
#                                    Endian, Deflated Explicit
#                                    VR Little Endian, JPEG
#                                    Baseline, JPEG Extended,
#                                    JPEG Lossless, JPEG 2000,
#                                    JPEG-LS, RLE Lossless,
#                                    MPEG2 / MPEG4 / HEVC,
#                                    SMPTE ST 2110-30 for
#                                    DICOM-RTV)
#     • `dicom-transfer-syntax-
#       registry`                    the typed registry of every
#                                    Transfer Syntax UID
#     • `dicom-parser`               the typed DICOM Data Set
#                                    streaming parser
#     • `dicom-object`               the typed `InMemDicomObject`
#                                    /  `FileDicomObject` /
#                                    `MemFileDicomObject` typed
#                                    DICOM-object API
#     • `dicom-dictionary-std`       the typed standard data
#                                    dictionary (every named
#                                    Tag from PS3.6 with its
#                                    VR + VM + name)
#     • `dicom-json`                 the typed DICOM-JSON
#                                    encoder + decoder (PS3.18
#                                    Annex F)
#     • `dicom-pixeldata`            the typed `PixelData`
#                                    extractor + decoder (with
#                                    support for every encoded
#                                    transfer syntax via
#                                    libdcm-decode bindings:
#                                    JPEG / JPEG 2000 / JPEG-LS
#                                    / RLE)
#     • `dicom-encoding-transfer-
#       syntax-jpeg2k` / `-jpegls`
#       / `-jpeg-baseline` / etc.    the typed JPEG / JPEG 2000
#                                    / JPEG-LS / RLE codec
#                                    adapters
#     • `dicom-ul`                   the typed DICOM Upper Layer
#                                    Protocol (UL) implementation
#                                    (the application-level
#                                    transport that wraps SOP
#                                    Class request/response
#                                    PDUs over TCP)
#     • `dicom-echoscu` / `findscu`
#       / `movescu` / `storescp` /
#       `storescu` / `scpproxy`      the canonical DCMTK-style
#                                    Service Class User / Service
#                                    Class Provider command-line
#                                    tools, ported to Rust
#                                    (already covered in this
#                                    completion corpus as the
#                                    existing dcmtk completions)
#     • `dicom-fromimage` / `toimage`  pixel-data conversion
#                                    tools between DICOM and
#                                    standard image formats
#                                    (PNG/JPG/TIFF)
#     • `dicom-dump`                 (this CLI tool)
#     • `devtools`                   internal codegen tools that
#                                    parse the DICOM standard
#                                    XML and generate the typed
#                                    dictionary code
#
#   Beyond `dicom-dump`, the `Enet4/dicom-rs` ecosystem powers
#   every modern Rust-based medical imaging tool:
#
#     • `LetsMelon/dicom-anonymizer` — DICOM file anonymization
#       CLI (PHI removal)
